entries.name: Verifier
entries.description: Implements the ZK proof verification logic.

entries.name: Governance
entries.description: Old Governance contract for ZKsync Era allowing for proposals in form of transactions. The minimum delay is 0s.

receivedPermissions.description: set addresses (validators) that can commit, prove, execute, revert batches through this contract.

entries.name: ZKsync
entries.description: The main contract defining the Layer 2. The operator commits blocks and provides a ZK proof which is validated by the Verifier contract and then processes transactions. During batch execution it processes L1 --> L2 and L2 --> L1 transactions.

issuedPermissions.description: commit, prove, execute, revert batches directly in the main Diamond contract. This role is typically held by a proxying ValidatorTimelock.
commit, prove, execute, revert batches directly in the main Diamond contract. This role is typically held by a proxying ValidatorTimelock.

txFilterer.description: This contract must expose the ITransactionFilterer interface (see Mailbox facet) and is used for censoring transactions pushed from L1 to L2.

getProtocolVersion.description: Protocol version, increments with each protocol upgrade.

getVerifierParams.description: Verifier parameters used for proving batches.

entries.name: L1ERC20Bridge_wstETH
entries.description: Bridge for depositing wrapped stETH (Lido) to ZKsync Era. These deposits and withdrawals do not go through the shared Bridge.

entries.name: L1ERC20Bridge
entries.description: Legacy bridge for depositing ERC20 tokens to ZKsync Era. Forwards deposits and withdrawals to the BridgeHub.

entries.name: ValidatorTimelock
entries.description: Intermediary contract between the *Validators* and the central diamond contract that delays block execution (ie withdrawals and other L2 --> L1 messages) by 3h.

receivedPermissions.description: commit, prove, execute, revert batches directly in the main Diamond contract. This role is typically held by a proxying ValidatorTimelock.

entries.name: ValidatorTimelockOld
entries.description: Intermediary contract between the *Validators* and the ZKsync Era diamond that delays block execution (ie withdrawals and other L2 --> L1 messages) by 21h. This contract is a remnant from pre Elastic Chain times.

issuedPermissions.description: set addresses (validators) that can commit, prove, execute, revert batches through this contract.

receivedPermissions.description: commit, prove, execute, revert batches directly in the main Diamond contract. This role is typically held by a proxying ValidatorTimelock.
